Q5 Remove any unwanted columns or outliers, standardize variables in pre-processing step¶

In [24]:
breast_df1=breast_df
breast_df.drop(['ID'],axis=1,inplace=True)


# We could see most of the outliers are now removed.

Out[25]:

In [26]:
## Outliers are present in Marginal Adhesion, Single Epithelial Cell Size, Normal Nucleoli, Bland Chromatin and Mitoses
Q1 = breast_df.quantile(0.25)
Q3 = breast_df.quantile(0.75)
IQR = Q3 - Q1
R1 = Q1 - (1.5*IQR)
R2 = Q3 + (1.5*IQR)
## R1 = mean - SD
## R2 = mean + SD
In [27]:
((breast_df<R1) | (breast_df>R2)).sum()

In [28]:
breast_df['Marginal Adhesion'] = np.where((breast_df['Marginal Adhesion'] < R1['Marginal Adhesion']) | (breast_df['Marginal Adhesion'] > R2['Marginal Adhesion']), breast_df['Marginal Adhesion'].median(),breast_df['Marginal Adhesion'])
breast_df['Single Epithelial Cell Size'] = np.where((breast_df['Single Epithelial Cell Size'] < R1['Single Epithelial Cell Size']) | (breast_df['Single Epithelial Cell Size'] > R2['Single Epithelial Cell Size']), breast_df['Single Epithelial Cell Size'].median(),breast_df['Single Epithelial Cell Size'])
breast_df['Normal Nucleoli'] = np.where((breast_df['Normal Nucleoli'] < R1['Normal Nucleoli'])|(breast_df['Normal Nucleoli'] > R2['Normal Nucleoli']), breast_df['Normal Nucleoli'].median(),breast_df['Normal Nucleoli'])
breast_df['Bland Chromatin'] = np.where((breast_df['Bland Chromatin'] < R1['Bland Chromatin'])|(breast_df['Bland Chromatin'] > R2['Bland Chromatin']), breast_df['Bland Chromatin'].median(),breast_df['Bland Chromatin'])

Q8 Find variance and cumulative variance by each eigen vector¶

In [41]:
## variance is Eigen Values
total = sum(eig_values)
In [42]:
sorted_eig_values=sorted(eig_values,reverse=True)
In [43]:
cum_var=[(val/total)*100 for val in sorted_eig_values]

In [57]:
## Step plot to visually see components significance
# Ploting 
plt.figure(figsize=(10 , 5))
plt.bar(range(1, eig_values.size + 1), cum_var, alpha = 0.5, align = 'center', label = 'Individual explained variance')
plt.step(range(1, eig_values.size + 1), cum_var_explained, where='mid', label = 'Cumulative explained variance')
plt.ylabel('Explained Variance Ratio')
plt.xlabel('Principal Components')
plt.legend(loc = 'best')
plt.tight_layout()
plt.show()
